'''Three referendums''' were held in [[Liechtenstein]] during 2009.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p 2057 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> The first two were held on 29 March and concerned reforming level I of secondary schooling and the introduction of a smoking ban in restaurants, both of which were rejected by voters. The third was held on 6 December on overturning a law introduced in May 2008 which placed an upper level on the electromagnetic field from phone masts,<ref>[http://www.mast-victims.org/index.php?content=news&action=view&type=country&id=188 News for Liechtenstein] Mast Victims</ref> and was approved by 57% of voters.<ref name=NS/>
