The '''Norwegian Medicines Agency''' (''Statens legemiddelverk'', ''Legemiddelverket'') is the national, regulatory authority for new and existing [[medicines]] and the [[supply chain]]. The Agency is responsible for supervising the production, [[Clinical trial|trials]] and [[marketing]] of medicines. It approves medicines and monitors their use, and ensures cost-efficient, effective and well-documented use of medicines. The inspectorate also supervises the supply-chain and regulates prices and trade conditions for pharmacies.
